WEEKLY.

Willis
Gaylord
Clark
was
born
in
Otisco,
in
the
county
of

Onondaga,
in
the
state
of
New
York.
He
was
the
son
of
a

soldier
in
the
days
of
the
Revolution,
and
writing
for
news

papers
and
periodicals
since
the
age
of
fourteen.
He
was

editor
of
the
Columbian
Star,
in
South
Carolina,
and
later

took
over
the
editorship
of
the
Philadelphia
Gazette.
He

wrote
for

New
York
Knickerbocker
Magazine
a
series

amusing
papers

quaint

Ollapodiana.

July,
1841,
an
account

a
